"orkney chair wikipedia";s:4:"slug";s:22:"orkney-chair-wikipedia";s:5:"title";s:54:"All About Orkney Chairs With Robert H Towers Northlink";s:3:"alt";s:17:"northlink ferries";s:3:"url";s:123:"https://www.northlinkferries.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/all_about_orkney_chairs_an_interview_with_robert_h_towers.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTjonYsznLz1rPFm9rft-YGlkclYm3cIhaX70f85IrmUOF6YsEqMxu6gVvIg7jBvxnxbos";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:1500;s:6:"height";i:1000;s:6:"source";s:71:"https://www.northlinkferries.co.uk/orkney-blog/all-about-orkney-chairs/";s:6:"domain";s:26:"www.northlinkferries.co.uk";}i:19;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:22:"orkney chair wikipedia";s:4:"slug";s:22:"orkney-chair-wikipedia";s:5:"title";s:67:"Orkney Isles Chair All Seating In 2021 Chair Seating Outdoor Chairs";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/736x/58/15/81/58158191fd019c7b6295423e1b916242.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:123:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSb7jeJaWtSsxbwAg0vDlImBAqsnQKX3rTVD5mKGIzy8VEDNhEV1c1AeK_SIpyofffHbkQ";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:736;s:6:"height";i:736;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/269371621452091008/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:22:"orkney chair wikipedia";s:4:"slug";s:22:"orkney-chair-wikipedia";s:5:"title";s:71:"Dunkeld Antiques Furniture Interior Design Mood Board Old Wooden Chairs";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/ab/38/e3/ab38e317fa2d5034833a5f7b04cfad83.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ8RtAtBCOkI2xDPM2LsmRLynbNKVKOu22IYg";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:634;s:6:"height";i:500;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/99008891779322526/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:75:{i:0;s:88:"The Orkney chair is a traditional piece of furniture dating back many hundreds of years.";i:1;s:185:"While many of the old straw crafts have died out the Orkney chair is still in production taking pride of place in the home of many Orcadians as well as being shipped all over the world.";i:2;s:385:"One of the basic pieces of furniture a chair is a type of seatIts primary features are two pieces of a durable material attached as back and seat to one another at a 90 or slightly greater angle with usually the four corners of the horizontal seat attached in turn to four legsor other parts of the seats underside attached to three legs or to a shaft about which a four-arm turnstile.";i:3;s:42:"The Orkney chair was designed around 1900.";i:4;s:39:"Orkney chair with beech and pine frame.";i:5;s:46:"The classic woven straw back on a sturdy seat.";i:6;s:38:"The arms are nicely curled at the end.";i:7;s:39:"This is a reproduction of the original.";i:8;s:33:"This one is at most 20 years old.";i:9;s:19:"106 cm Seat height.";i:10;s:21:"44 cm Armrest height.";i:11;s:21:"63 cm Length x width.";i:12;s:51:"61 x 64 cm The chair can be picked up in Rotterdam.";i:13;s:197:"T he Orkney chair has developed through local tradition perhaps originating from a simple piece of furniture that the islanders could make for themselves with what materials were readily available.";i:14;s:88:"I n its very early stages it was nothing more than a low round stool covered with straw.";i:15;s:95:"It was then developed into a low chair by the addition of a straw back some two feet in height.";i:16;s:25:"Welcome to Orkney Chairs.";i:17;s:38:"S ince 1977 master craftsman Robert H.";i:18;s:109:"Towers has been making and exporting beautifully handcrafted examples of the Orkney Chair all over the world.";i:19;s:103:"T hese unique straw-backed Orkney chairs are famous as part of the rich heritage of the Orkney Islands.";i:20;s:42:"On this site you can learn about Robert H.";i:21;s:67:"Towers craft view his workmanship and contact him to enquire about.";i:22;s:32:"The history of the Orkney chair.";i:23;s:109:"The origins of the Orkney chair lie in the shortage of raw materials for both building and furnishing houses.";i:24;s:104:"Before improved transport links in the mid-1800s brought manufactured goods to the islands their remote.";i:25;s:29:"44 0 7742 428727 Enquire now.";i:26;s:83:"Come and visit our workshop in Kirkwall to witness a craft centuries in the making.";i:27;s:141:"Our range of Orkney furniture brings the past and present together maintaining modern day links with the history and heritage of our islands.";i:28;s:47:"The only chair made completely by hand on site.";i:29;s:74:"An Orkney Chair is unique part of the rich heritage of the Orkney Islands.";i:30;s:50:"They are wooden handcrafted and have a straw back.";i:31;s:40:"We approached master craftsman Robert H.";i:32;s:91:"Towers who has been making Orkney Chairs for over 38 years to ask him some questions about.";i:33;s:32:"Stoneywell and the Orkney Chair.";i:34;s:84:"When two design disciplines meet perfectly the results can be something spectacular.";i:35;s:203:"This is the case with Stoneywell a property designed by the furniture designer Ernest Gimson in the Arts and Crafts style and the Orkney chair which encompasses the ethos of the Arts and Crafts movement.";i:36;s:17:"So yes The Chair.";i:37;s:139:"Celtic Connections once said we combine a benignly hedonistic version of Viking berserker spirit with a formidable breadth of musicianship.";i:38;s:20:"We quite liked that.";i:39;s:29:"Oh and there are eight of us.";i:40;s:38:"Not only quality but quantity as well.";i:41;s:92:"The Orkney chair is probably one of the most iconic pieces of Scottish vernacular furniture.";i:42;s:131:"Now highly collectable with examples at the Victoria Albert Museum Orkney chairs were originally made with a very practical design.";i:43;s:106:"The chair style that we know today was standardised in the mid-19th century by David Kirkness of Kirkwall.";i:44;s:60:"Welcome to Scapa Crafts makers of traditional Orkney chairs.";i:4